OL,3,CWhy headteachers are concerned Ofsted
OL,4,Creports could cause more tragedies
OL,6,FIn a statement, Chief Inspector Sir
OL,7,FMartyn Oliver said: "I am very sorry
OL,8,Fto hear that these head teachers feel
OL,9,Fthe way they do. Our new framework has
OL,10,Fbeen designed with head teachers'
OL,11,Fwellbeing firmly in mind. And our
OL,12,Finspectors all complete mental health
OL,13,Ftraining that helps them recognise and
OL,14,Frespond to signs of distress.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G23/29
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31224
SC,0024
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1783973917
OL,3,CWhy headteachers are concerned Ofsted
OL,4,Creports could cause more tragedies
OL,6,F"However, I cannot remove all the
OL,7,Fpressure from the inspection process.
OL,8,FOur priority is always the education
OL,9,Fand welfare of children. That means
OL,10,Fholding schools to account and,
OL,11,Fsometimes, conveying difficult
OL,12,Fmessages where standards are not high
OL,13,Fenough.
OL,15,F"I am pleased that a great many school
OL,16,Fleaders have told us that inspection
OL,17,Fnow feels more collaborative and
OL,18,Fconstructive. But we take all feedback
OL,19,Fseriously and we will continue to
OL,20,Flisten."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G24/29
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
